Description:
FLAWLESSLY RENOVATED WITH A WAREHOUSE CONVERSION TWIST
Captivating sun drenched apartment with customised high-end features and stunning views.
- 2 large bedrooms featuring custom built-in robes, 100% wool carpet, Nobo heaters
- Beautifully renovated kitchen with Messmate hardwood benchtops, Bosch appliances, USB power
- Living and dining complimented perfectly with polished concrete floors, built-in hardwood shelving, premium Daikin split system
- Immaculately renovated bathroom with Methven tapware, heated towel rail, European laundry
- Enjoy city views from a private balcony streaming off the living area
- Secure gated parking and additional parking permits for guests
- In a block of only 11, with new windows and doors throughout
Be quick to secure your slice of bustling Collingwood! This brilliant inner city locale is walking distance to Johnston and Smith Street's fabulous cafes, restaurants, and shops - as well as trains, buses, trams, the Yarra River bike trails, and much much more.

Description:
Investment opportunity with a difference
This second-level 2 BDR apartment is part of the prominent former grain silos landmark in Collingwood. Comprising stylish gourmet kitchen, featuring stone benches, S/S appliances, including dishwasher, glass splashback and solid cabinetry, living space with a sizeable north-facing balcony, modern tiled bathroom. Extras include quality carpets, storage cage, car space, heating/cooling, European laundry, large outdoor undercover entertainment decking, BBQ and gym facilities, intercom and secure entrance. The Islington Silos make a defining contribution to the emergence of Collingwood as a highly coveted residential locale, with numerous cafes and bars, including, Naked For Satan, Jimmy Grant's, The Gem Bar, Stomping Ground Brewery and Beer Hall, local galleries, Collingwood Leisure Centre, a short walk to Abbotsford Convent and the Yarra Trail, schools and easy access to tram to the CBD, and the Eastern and Monash freeways.
Insights: 109/55 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Stylish Residential with Commercial Potential
Built in 1900 this elegant Victorian shopfront and dwelling on Johnston Street offers limitless potential as a cafe, design studio, gallery or business. Ideal for dual tenancy with a stylish residence it is packed with original features. The large shopfront onto Johnston features parquetry floors, high ceilings, rosettes and double glazed windows. Continuing the theme is a separate sitting/dining room with baltic pine floors, an enchanting fireplace and sculpted wood mantel. This leads to the architect designed light filled kitchen with split system, S/S appliances, sleek cabinetry and island bench offering views and access to the deck and landscaped rear garden. A decorative balustrade leads to a light filled upper level with three spacious bedrooms. The north-facing master bedroom boasts an original fireplace with spectacular marble mantelpiece, decorative ceiling and large double glazed windows. Extras include, OSP via secure roller door onto ROW, new street awning, quality carpets and modern tiled bathroom, laundry and second w/c. A short walk to Abbotsford Convent and the Yarra Trail there are also several public transport options outside your door, including train and bus to the CBD, abundant cafes, eateries and specialty shops, Collingwood Leisure Centre, schools and easy access to the Eastern and Monash fwys. Nothing to spend. (Commercial Zone 1).
Insights: 163 Johnston Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2018 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
The perfect inner-city living environment
Set at the rear, beyond original factory walls, this spacious top floor 2 level warehouse style property flooded with natural light provides the perfect sanctuary for the busy professional or those looking to soak up the wonderful inner-city lifestyle that this superb position affords you. As you enter the property you are immediately drawn to the expansive open plan interior showcasing separate living, dining and relaxing zones along with a family-sized gourmet kitchen and island breakfast bar - all enjoying floor to ceiling glass windows and doors that offer views and access to a large entertainer's terrace and original red brick factory walls. The 1st floor includes a huge master bedroom with walk-in robe and modern bathroom & 2nd bedroom with built-in robe. Both bedrooms enjoy large framed stylish windows and access to a 2nd stylish bathroom. Other features include 3 x split system heating/cooling units, separate powder room & laundry, security foyer entrance, secure off-street parking & storage cage. The wonderful location offers easy access to the vibrant Smith St, Brunswick St & Gertrude St specialty shops, popular cafes & restaurants, transport, parklands and a short walk to the CBD. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Take your first bright step
Northerly light illuminates the entire interior of this apartment positioned in Collingwood's trendy heart, and offers first homebuyers a dream lifestyle within steps to Smith Street's cafes.
Making a city edge statement, this first floor apartment with off street parking is set in a block of only six. It features a bedroom with a built-in robe, a neat bathroom with laundry facilities, and a beautifully bright lounge room/casual dining area is overseen by a renovated contemporary kitchen where the mosaic-tiled splashback steals the limelight as it adds a vibrant splash of colour!
The location does not get better than this as trams, cafes, restaurants, Edinburgh Gardens, the CBD, bars and easy freeway access makes this an exceptional first home, investment or downsizing opportunity.
